NAME
  manlocalpdf - creates a PDF file of the given manpage subject from the current folder
SYNOPSIS
  manlocalpdf [subject]
DESCRIPTION
  manlocalpdf converts a given manual page subject to a PDF file of the same
  name in the current folder using the man(1) and ps2pdf(1) utilities.
  This variant uses the current folder as the manpage source, which can
  be useful for converting pages for operating systems other than the
  currently-installed one.
SEE ALSO
  man(1), ps2pdf(1)
  
AUTHOR
  Ryan Armstrong <software@zerker.ca>
